<text_item id="lb" component_id="lb_01" visible="false">
<value>Authentication</value>
<behavior id="clickOnShowPopup1" target="pb_01"/>
<behavior id="clickOnShowGraphic1" target="gi_02"/>
<style/>
</text_item>
<audio_item visible="true" id="audioi" category="" contCategory="" contID="" allowMultiple="true" allowMultiplesLimit="9" component_id="audioi_02" characterSelected="false" file="t38_aud_0088.spx"/>
<text_item id="pb" component_id="pb_01" visible="false">
<value>Authentication is the process of one user, application, or computer verifying its identity to another. This is usually done with a username and password combination, a smart card, or a PIN. In the case of web services, authentication usually occurs between applications using certificates or passwords.</value>
<behavior id="playAudio2" target="audioi_02"/>
<style x="-388" y="-107"/>
</text_item>
<text_item id="lb" component_id="lb_02" visible="false">
<value>Authorization</value>
<behavior id="clickOnShowPopup1" target="pb_02"/>
<behavior id="clickOnShowGraphic1" target="gi_03"/>
<style/>
</text_item>
<audio_item visible="true" id="audioi" category="" contCategory="" contID="" allowMultiple="true" allowMultiplesLimit="9" component_id="audioi_03" characterSelected="false" file="t38_aud_0089.spx"/>
<text_item id="pb" component_id="pb_02" visible="false">
<value>Authorization involves checking whether an authenticated user, application, or computer has permissions to access a requested resource. |n  |n Resources can include XML web services, files, or databases. They're typically categorized by role or type and have specific access levels assigned to them. During authorization, the requesting entity's permissions are measured against the resource's access level. If the entity has adequate permissions, access is granted â€“ and if not, access is denied.</value>
<behavior id="playAudio2" target="audioi_03"/>
<style x="-388" y="-107"/>
</text_item>
<text_item id="lb" component_id="lb_03" visible="false">
<value>Auditing and logging</value>
<behavior id="clickOnShowPopup1" target="pb_03"/>
<behavior id="clickOnShowGraphic1" target="gi_04"/>
<style/>
</text_item>
<text_item id="pb" component_id="pb_03" visible="false">
<value>Computer systems can perform auditing and logging operations to record information about attempts to access resources. You can use this information to troubleshoot system issues. |n  |n You can perform auditing and logging on different system components, such as web servers, database servers, and operating systems. When you're working on web service security, the transport layer accessing a service is a prime candidate for logging operations.</value>
<behavior id="playAudio2" target="audioi_04"/>
<style x="-388" y="-107"/>
</text_item>
